Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, indicating significant renal impairment. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) suggest possible urinary tract pathology. Elevated urine glucose and ketones with low HbA1c may reflect acute metabolic disturbance rather than chronic hyperglycemia. Mild hyperchloremia is present. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease, metabolic derangement, and possible urinary tract infection or obstruction.
